      "id": "PopularPost187471",
      "post_content": "Great sideboard choice for Parfait decks (mono-white with [Orim's Chant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Orim's Chant) and such) that also sees play in Enchantress enchantment-heavy decks. Sits well in a protection-oriented build alongside [Runed Halo](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Runed Halo) and [True Believer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=True Believer). Got bumped from uncommon to rare.  \n  \nAnd this one's the copy to get. Gorgeous art by Alan Pollack (who is also the only artist to paint [Circle of Protection: Green](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=11202) so well that you might actually want to own a copy of Circle of Protection: Green). Like COP:Green, this card's aesthetic value was marred a little by the white border printing. Wizards, you could always reprint this in a future core set! You could bump the rarity up again to Mythic!",
      "posted_by": "Salient",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost187471\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Great sideboard choice for Parfait decks (mono-white with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Orim's Chant\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Orim's Chant\">Orim's Chant</a> and such) that also sees play in Enchantress enchantment-heavy decks. Sits well in a protection-oriented build alongside <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Runed Halo\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Runed Halo\">Runed Halo</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"True Believer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=True Believer\">True Believer</a>. Got bumped from uncommon to rare.<br/><br/>And this one's the copy to get. Gorgeous art by Alan Pollack (who is also the only artist to paint <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"11202\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=11202\">Circle of Protection: Green</a> so well that you might actually want to own a copy of Circle of Protection: Green). Like COP:Green, this card's aesthetic value was marred a little by the white border printing. Wizards, you could always reprint this in a future core set! You could bump the rarity up again to Mythic!</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '187471'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                       